Eskom can’t seem to catch a break even when they are surprisingly honouring their promise of not implementing load shedding during the festive season. For now at least. It was revealed yesterday that their Kendal power station in Mpumalanga has been served with a notice to shut down two of its units by 9 January, having not met a number of emissions and environmental compliances. Kendal is the largest indirect dry-cooled power station in the world. “We have given plans to the authorities on what we had planned to do. We’ve met some of those plans but not all of...